British-born Nigerian songwriter and music producer, KaniBeatz has hinted at collaborations with music stars such as Joeboy and Oxlade in 2022. KaniBeatz whose work in 2021 “Gba Gbe” peaked at No 45 on Apple Music Top 10, released snippets of what to expect in the new year while promising to wow his fans in 2022. Going into the new year, KaniBeatz expressed optimism 2022 is a big year for him, as he plans collaborations with artists such as Oxlade, Joeboy, Prettyboy-Do, YKB, and UK artists, including Backroad Gee, Jay1, and many others. The plan, according to him, is to release most of the collaborations this year.   Burna Boy demands a united Africa     How I handle social media trolls, says Waje     Wande Coal says fame intoxicates   He said his priority is nothing but quality music, just as he promised that he would always release snippets of new songs on his social media handles. - Advertisement - KaniBeatz, who is making a bold statement in the Nigerian music industry and the global music scene, has released an exhilarating sound that falls between the popular afrobeat sound of his native Nigeria, and the catchy and ever-evolving afro-swing scene that has dominated British charts in recent years. KaniBeatz started off January 2021 with a bang with the release of his first body of work, an EP entitled “Chrystical” with the talented songstress Bella Alubo. The lead single of the project titled “Gba Gbe” featured Abuja rapper PsychoYP and East African superstar Lava Lava. Kanibeatz has also released snippets of upcoming collaborations with artists such as Oxlade, Prettyboy-Do, and Joeboy in 2022.